An Act to eliminate discrimination of incarcerated persons' participation in life saving programs.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Subsection (a) of section 236 of chapter 111 of the General Laws, as
2 appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the word “gift.” in
3 line 21, the following words: including, but not limited to incarcerated persons of 18 years of
4 age.
5 SECTION 2. Said section 236 of said chapter 111, as so appearing, is amended by
6 inserting after the word “care” in line 143, the following words: The Department of Corrections
7 shall provide a caregiver at the covered entity or correctional facility to provide all necessary
8 aftercare and continuing care pursuant to this section as if the location were a residence.
9 SECTION 3. Said section 236 of Chapter 111, as so appearing, is hereby amended by
10 adding the following subsection at line 213:-(g) Pursuant to the nondiscriminatory requirements
11 of this section, the Department of Corrections shall promulgate procedures to allow persons
12 incarcerated in the Commonwealth to become a living organ donor, receive an organ transplant,
